result.name: Oscar Kitchen 雄記

reviews.text: Went there after lunch to have freshly ground coffee and a brownie with ice cream. Coffee and dessert taste good, it serves different kind of main course dishes too like sandwiches and spaghetti etc. Sure I will go back again to try those. Pets allowed and cash only.
They chief make the food with passion and heart

Found this little cosy cafe on the heritage trail. Nice cakes and coffee. Price very reasonable. Wonderful nougat apricot bavarois, which costs only $25. Pasta is homemade by owner who previously ran a private kitchen. He makes it in the very early morning every day. Worthy to try. Seafood pasta and red wine stewed beef are both good.
Fine wine and fine food, better than those offer in 6 star hotel
A small café operated by a dedicated team.
